            <title>[HBASE-17130] Add support to specify an arbitrary number of reducers when writing HFiles for bulk load</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-17130</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;From the discussion from &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-16894&quot; title=&quot;Create more than 1 split per region, generalize HBASE-12590&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-16894&quot;&gt;HBASE-16894&lt;/a&gt; there is a set of use cases where writing to multiple regions in a single reducer can be helpful to reduce the overhead of MR jobs when a large number of regions exist in an HBase cluster and some regions can present a data skew, e.g. 100s or 1000s of regions with a very small number of rows vs. regions with 10s or millions or rows as part of the same job. And merging regions is not an option for the use case.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
